  <!-- SURFERS TRAVEL -->
  <center>
    <div class="portfolio-modal modal fade" id="surfers" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="modal-dialog h-100">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="close-modal" data-dismiss="modal">
            <div class="lr">
              <div class="rl"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
                <div class="modal-body">
                  <img src="img/portfolio/Surf.png" width="180px"></img>
                  <h4>The <a href="https://twitter.com/search?f=tweets&vertical=default&q=%23surf&src=typd">#surf</a>
                    project.</h4>
                  <p style="max-width: 600px">I recovered tweets containing <a
                      href="https://twitter.com/search?f=tweets&vertical=default&q=%23surf&src=typd">#surf</a> for 9
                    months. Here is where surfers travel.</p>
                  <br><br>
                  <div style="text-align: left">
                    <h6>Description</h6>
                    <hr>
                    <p>I created an <code>R</code> script that recovers all tweets containing the hashtags
                      <code>#surf</code> and run it on a webserver for about 9 months. I recovered more than 400k
                      tweets. Some of them being geolocalized for both home and current location, it is possible to
                      deduce where surfers travel.</p>
                    <p>Here is an overview of the result:</p>
                    <a href="https://www.data-to-viz.com/story/MapConnection.html">
                      <center><img src="img/portfolio/surf_travel.png" width="80%"></img></center>
                    </a>
                    <h6>Read more</h6>
                    <hr>
                    <span>See the dedicated page in <a
                        href="https://www.data-to-viz.com/story/MapConnection.html">data-to-viz.com</a> that tells
                      more about this project, with explanation on how to build a <a
                        href="https://www.data-to-viz.com/story/MapConnection.html">connection map</a>.</span>
                    <br><br><br>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
  </center>






